post_text:
1,500 emergency food boxes and an assortment of fresh produce will be made available in a Drive Through Food Distribution this Saturday, June 27th beginning at 9:30 am on a first come first serve basis in the parking lot of Novo Nordisk at 800 Scudders Mill Road in Plainsboro.

Recipients must show proof of NJ residency (driver’s license or utility bill) and clean out the trunk of their car prior to arriving. One allocation will be provided per vehicle. While the event is focused on Middlesex County no one will be turned away from receiving food as long as they have proof of NJ residency!

post_text: Carteret Schools declares June 17, 2020 Rambler Day! Help us celebrate our students, especially our CHS Class of 2020 Seniors, CMS Grade 8 and elementary Grades 5, Grades K and Prek by stepping outside at 8:20pm (20:20 Military time) and applauding in unison. Have your children join you outside, so your fellow neighbors may applaud them. Show your Rambler pride: Decorate your homes and cars in Rambler Blue & White, wear Rambler clothing, make posters, tie ribbons, honk your horns and make some noise! Join us Wednesday, June 17th @ 8:20pm!

post_text: At 2NDFLOOR Youth Helpline, we are fully operational and are here to offer support to NJ youth by text/phone and message boards 24 hours a day. The majority of our recent contacts have been connected to stress and worries about the COVID 19 virus and functioning through this period. Our staff is prepared and able to offer support and resources specific to the virus and any other issue or concern that may be presented.

The time has arrived! Our very own 5th grade ELA teacher, Sara Jimenez, is going to be doing a lesson on NJ Learning Live on Reading Fun with Nonfiction Texts and Summaries. Check it out on your local access channel OR watch on https://www.njtvonline.org/programs/njtv-learning-live/

Let's support her and tune in! If you take any selfies or pictures watching her be sure to share with us so we can post and celebrate her representing Nathan Hale and Carteret! Congratulations Sara - we are so proud! #RamblersRise

post_text:
Due to COVID-19, we are unable to do our production live for an audience. Luckily we filmed one of our final dress rehearsals and are happy to share it with you all. CHS Drama Club is excited to finally launch our "Anywhere Seat" account, in which you will be able to pay for an access code to watch of our production of Once On This Island.

By going to chsdrama.anywhereseat.com <http://chsdrama.anywhereseat.com/>, you will be prompted to "Name Your Price" (anywhere from $5.00- $100.00) for an access code to view this production. All access codes are unique to each device so if you would like to view on multiple devices, you will have to obtain a new access code. Please consider support the CHS Drama Club! #ramblersrise

post_text: We just wanted to remind our Faculty and Staff that they are doing a “Good Job. ” Thank you for all you do. Happy Teacher Appreciation Week! #Ramblersrise
shared_text:
Alicia Keys
April 24 at 12:56 AM ·

Can’t believe that this song I wrote months ago... is sooo relevant now. I wrote it for all the people that work so hard and never hear the words “Good Job” ⁣
⁣
I believe in us though, I believe in the way we are showing up for each other and caring about each other. The way that we are all connected more than we’ve ever been before. This is for you. You’re doing a good job! 👏🏽 👏🏽 👏🏽 ⁣
⁣
Endless love to Swizz, The Dream and Avenue Beatz for creating these beautiful words and music with me 💜💜Thank you CNN

Be Counted

For the first time, you can complete the #2020Census online. And given so many of us are working remotely, we recommend scheduling this task on your list of to-do's. Make sure everyone in your home is counted! The Census count affects the allocation of funding for your community’s public resources and planning for the future.

To learn more, visit 2020census.gov.

post_text: Another competition, another VICTORY! This weekend four of our Carteret Schools Odyssey of the Mind Teams put their months of hard work and dedication to the test and competed at Sayreville War Memorial High School against over 15 other teams across Central New Jersey. After a long day of competing, both long term and spontaneous problems, 2 of our 4 teams are moving on to STATE FINALS on Saturday April 4, 2020 at Princeton High School. Congratulations to each and every one of them and good luck at State Finals!

post_text: CHS Varsity Vocals WON THE ICHSA NORTHEAST QUARTERFINAL!!!! Varsity Vocals took first place with a score of 402. In addition to being 1st Place Champions, Amy Casale & Jasmin Langomas recieved the award for Outstanding Choreography and Kevin Caballero recieved the award for Outstanding Vocal Percussion! They will be advancing to the ICHSA Semifinals at Mechanics Hall in Massachusetts on March 22nd! We are so incredibly proud of the talent and hard work of this amazing group. You’ve made CHS and your director proud!

AJ Silvestri set a new personal record for collected wishes -

211,729 !!!

Of that total, We are very proud to say that 7,212 of those wishes came from the Carteret School District. WE MADE A DIFFERENCE TODAY! The ripple effect put out into the community will be felt not only by the children whose wishes will be granted, but by the people who will be inspired to help in the future with this heartwarming endeavor.

post_text:
Parents please be advised of the following:

Happy Halloween! pursuant to local municipal law, Trick or Treating is authorized in the Carteret until 7 pm tonight, Thursday, October 31st 2019. Any child 13 or under may Trick or Treat until 6 pm unless accompanied by an adult. If accompanied by an adult they may Trick or Treat until 7pm. The Borough advises residents to not open their doors past 7 pm as Trick or Treating is not permitted past 7pm.

The Borough also invites you to participate in the annual PBA/ HPBA Rag-A-Muffin parade at Sullivan field on Carteret Ave at Carteret Park tonight at 6pm. This event open to the public is sponsored by the men and women of the Carteret Police Dept’s PBA #47 and their sponsors and supporters

post_text:
Junior from Carteret High School, Haniyfa Larkins wins the Central Jersey Student Leadership Award
Haniyfa Larkins, a junior at Carteret High School, is an active member in several Pathways and school clubs as well as the community Teen Advisory Board Committee. On May 16th, Haniyfa was honored with the Planned Parenthood Student Leadership Award at the Central New Jersey Teen Conference. At the age of 16, Haniyfa embodies what leadership and empowerment look like.
Note: The banner hanging in the background which was on display throughout the conference was done by Max Lopez, senior at CHS

post_text:
CHS Student Gets Top Award

Araly Langomas, a junior at Carteret High School was one of the artists chosen for the State Exhibition at the Capital House in Trenton. Araley's work was one of 6 pieces chosen out of 87 from Middlesex County to be included in the State level exhibit. She was recognized for work and dedication to visual arts at a reception held on March 8th.
Araley's piece, which was created in Mrs. Perez's Design class was part of an assignment on Surrealism and illustrates a woman's perspective while approaching motherhood.
Congratulations Araly!
